<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6217ded9-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s115"><num value="115">§ 115.</num><heading> Payment of annuities in goods</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may, at the request of any Indian tribe, to which an annuity is payable in money, cause the same to be paid in goods, purchased as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s91">section 91 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6217deda-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(R.S. § 2082.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6217dedb-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6217dedc-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id6217dedd-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/usc/t25/s91">Section 91 of this title</ref>, referred to in text, was omitted from the Code.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id6217dede-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 2082 derived from <ref href="/us/act/1834-06-30/ch162/s12">act June 30, 1834, ch. 162, § 12</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/4/737">4 Stat. 737</ref>.</p>
</note>
